    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras face a challenging slate today, with several high-end arms like Chris Sale, Paul Skenes, and Tarik Skubal creating significant resistance for our core hitters. Despite the tough matchups, **Yordan Alvarez** (77.33) and **Colt Keith** (68.51) emerge as our top anchors. **Yordan Alvarez** benefits from a favorable matchup against a pedestrian starter in Pallante, while **Colt Keith**\u2019s position in the three-hole combined with a solid platoon advantage gives him the highest ceiling in today\u2019s lineup. We are also leaning into the speed-to-score pipeline with **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (64.51); despite hitting 8th, his high dynamic platoon grade and the opposing pitcher\u2019s slow delivery create a massive stolen base opportunity, which is vital given our strategic emphasis on speed.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision involved keeping **Caleb Durbin** (42.48) in the lineup despite the brutal matchup against Skubal. While his total score hovered near the bottom of our starters, his 42% stolen base projection remains too valuable to bench in a 5x5 format where speed is the primary scarcity. **Junior Caminero** (53.51) barely held onto his spot against Skenes; though he faces an elite arm, his elevated order position provides enough volume to justify the start over reserves. Unfortunately, we remain hamstrung by the status of **Christian Yelich**, who remains on the IL, and **Victor Scott II**, who sits on the bench today due to a lack of a confirmed starting slot, despite his elite projection profile for stealing bases. Monitor **Trea Turner** (56.27) and **Kyle Schwarber** (54.53) closely; both face a formidable Sale, but their elite xwOBA metrics and leadoff/two-hole positions provide enough structural support to weather the matchup risk.",
